    "description": "We at Piramal Pharma Global Group are looking for an experienced Surgeon based out of Nashik. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Piramal Pharma Global Group:\nPiramal Pharma Global Group is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Flexible working hours\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Nashik, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Piramal Pharma Global Group!",
